Welcome! I am a MASc student at The Edward S. Rogers Sr. Department of Electrical & Computer Engineering (ECE), University of Toronto, Canada. My advisor is Prof. Baochun Li. Prior to this, I spent four wonderful years at Hongyi Honor College, Wuhan University (WHU), China, and got my B.E. degree there. I worked with Prof. Yanjiao Chen during my undergraduate studies.

My research interests lie at the intersections of networking and communication and machine learning, especially deep reinforcement learning (DRL) and federated learning (FL).
